# Collaboration Standards

## Git Workflow
- **Branch Strategy**: main (protected), feature/[name], fix/[name], docs/[name]
- **Commit Messages**: Use format `type(scope): description`
  - Examples: `feat(website): add new ZAG Matrix component`, `fix(blog): resolve MDX rendering issue`
- **PR Process**: Create feature branch → focused changes → descriptive PR → review → merge

## Code Standards
- **TypeScript**: Use strict mode, proper type definitions, functional components with hooks
- **React**: Follow Next.js 13+ App Router patterns
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS, responsive design, consistent spacing/typography
- **File Organization**: 
  - Components: [website/components/](mdc:website/components/)
  - Pages: [website/app/](mdc:website/app/)
  - Blog posts: [website/posts/](mdc:website/posts/)
  - Content: [content/](mdc:content/)
  - Tests: [tests/](mdc:tests/)

## Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `ZagMatrixSidebar.tsx`)
- **Files**: kebab-case (e.g., `zag-matrix-page.tsx`)
- **Functions**: camelCase (e.g., `handleNewsletterSignup`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `ZAG_MATRIX_PILLARS`)

## Brand Consistency
- **ZAG Matrix Framework**: All content must connect to ZEN, ACT, GEM
- **Target Audience**: "Alex, the Awakened Technologist" - mid-career professionals seeking purpose
- **Tone**: Professional but approachable, confident, actionable insights
- **Examples**: Include specific examples from Sheridan's career

## Communication
- **Primary**: Email for longer-form updates and planning
- **Project Updates**: GitHub Issues/PRs for code discussions
- **Quick Questions**: Slack DM when both online
- **No Fixed Schedule**: Flexible, ad-hoc collaboration
- **Response Time**: 24-48 hours for email, few days for GitHub Issues

## Quality Assurance
Before submitting PRs:
- [ ] Code follows TypeScript and React best practices
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Responsive design works on multiple screen sizes
- [ ] Brand consistency maintained
- [ ] ZAG Matrix framework integrated appropriately
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed
